## EXAMPLE MODEL: 6-MONTH REVENUE PROJECTION

### Assumptions
- Starting retainer clients: 3 at $1,500/mo average
- New clients per month: 2 (base), 3 (best), 1 (worst)
- Average implementation per new client: $6,000
- Monthly fixed costs: $8,000 (team + tools + ops)
- Churn: 5% monthly (base), 2% (best), 10% (worst)

### Base Case — Monthly Breakdown

| Month | New Clients | Total Retainer Clients | Impl. Revenue | MRR | Total Revenue | Total Costs | Net Profit |
|-------|------------|----------------------|---------------|-----|---------------|-------------|------------|
| M1 | 2 | 5 | $12,000 | $7,500 | $19,500 | $8,000 | $11,500 |
| M2 | 2 | 7 | $12,000 | $10,500 | $22,500 | $8,500 | $14,000 |
| M3 | 2 | 9 | $12,000 | $13,500 | $25,500 | $9,000 | $16,500 |
| M4 | 2 | 11 | $12,000 | $16,500 | $28,500 | $9,500 | $19,000 |
| M5 | 2 | 13 | $12,000 | $19,500 | $31,500 | $10,000 | $21,500 |
| M6 | 2 | 15 | $12,000 | $22,500 | $34,500 | $10,500 | $24,000 |

**6-Month Totals:**
- Total Revenue: $162,000
- Total Costs: $55,500
- Total Net Profit: $106,500
- Ending MRR: $22,500 | Ending ARR: $270,000

### Plain English Summary
At a steady pace of 2 new clients per month, Vertex Automation reaches 15 retainer
clients and $22,500 MRR by month 6. Implementation revenue provides strong upfront
cash flow while the retainer base compounds. Net profit margins improve from ~59% to
~70% as fixed costs are absorbed by growing revenue. This trajectory puts ARR above
$270K without any team expansion. The key risk is client churn — keeping it below 5%
monthly is critical to hitting these numbers.

